President Biden welcomed President Ramaphosa of South Africa to the White House, expressing admiration for the country and its long struggle for freedom and justice. They discussed the shared values between the United States and South Africa and the need for a deeper understanding between the two nations. President Biden commended South Africa's leadership on climate, health, and COVID-19, and expressed the desire to see the country produce COVID insulin on the continent. They also discussed trade relations and the importance of addressing global challenges such as food security and stability and security in the region. President Ramaphosa thanked the United States for its support in fighting COVID-19 and advocated for the finalization of negotiations on therapeutics and diagnostics. They also touched on gender empowerment and the issue of climate change, particularly in relation to a just transition. Both leaders expressed gratitude for the opportunity to discuss these issues and looked forward to further discussions.